question = Question.create(catagory_id: catagory.id, topic_id: topic.id, question_num: "3", question_content: "Which material below is both STIFF and STRONG?", question_image: "section_images/strengthstiffness.png", explanation: "Strength is a different materials property than stiffness, although they may sound similar. Strength refers to the amount of force or stress required to break something. Stiffness is a measure of the inherent elasticity (or stretchiness) of a material. For example, rubber has a very low measure of stiffness - it's not very stiff at all - while diamond has a very high measure of stiffness. A cracker is stiff but not strong - it will break very easily. Jello is not stiff at all. Nylon is very strong, but not stiff at all! Steel is both stiff and strong. We build bridges and buildings out of materials that are both stiff and strong. ")
