question = Question.create(catagory_id: catagory.id, topic_id: topic.id, question_num: "3", question_content: "What is the main ingredient in glass?", question_image: "section_images/sand_castle.jpg", explanation: "The main ingredient in most glass is a compound called silicon dioxide, also known as silica. Silica is also the main ingredient in sand. Sand and glass look nothing alike, but sand heated up to very high temperatures forms glass! To make glass, other ingredients are added to the silica sand. These ingredients are added to change and improve the properties of the glass. Chemicals can also be added to change the color of glass. The mixture is then heated to high temperatures to melt and become glass. Because glass is sand heated to very high temperatures, glass can found in nature near very hot sources. One example of naturally occurring glass comes from lightning striking sand.")
